text.tspan: 01. Add icon to this file in one of the empty slots
02. Ensure it fits on the pixel grid
04. Leave a minimum of 1px white space between fills
05. Expand all lines to fills and unite all shapes to one path
07. Give the icon a CSS class name. Use a “-” to separate name parts
08. Update the date above to todays date
09. Name the artboard with the CSS class (not the icon bit though)
10. Hide the pixel ‘Grid’ group of layers
12. When exporting use the file name ‘.svg’ (the icon prefix gets added in ico.mo)
13. Upload new svg’s at the end of the Fidelity Icon Font on icomoon.io
14. Give the correct names on Icomoon and ensure the unicodes match the codes in the image to the right >>
15. Add new unicodes to the new icons in Icomoon
17. Ensure the dev team use the new unicodes you have specified in Icomoo (viewable in the demo html)
